<HEAD>Impressionist Painting Stolen From Museum</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUNTINGTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 108-year-old oil painting by French Impressionist <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Manet </PERSON> was stolen from a display in an art museum. The painting, titled `` Bouquet of Peonies,'' was stolen Sunday afternoon from the Heckscher Art Museum in this <LOCATION> Long </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> town, said Officer <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON>, a police spokesman. The still life, which depicts an arrangement of flowers in a vase, was of `` high, unspecified value,'' <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Manet </PERSON> finished the 16-by-22-inch oil-on-canvas piece in 1880.
