ompanies, and is better than the health care coverage at <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> McDonnell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION>.'' <PERSON> Almeida </PERSON> said negotiators accepted the cut in health benefits `` based on the way negotiations have been going throughout the country.'' <PERSON> Almeida </PERSON> said he understood from the negotiations that the new 80-20 provision will eventually affect all <ORGANIZATION> UTC </ORGANIZATION> workers. He estimated that the policy, when applied to the entire corporation, will save <ORGANIZATION> UTC </ORGANIZATION> $ 30 to $ 40 million per year.
